<p>I searched the support forums but I did not found anything related to my issue.</p>
<p>WooCommerce has some at least one issue with W3TC regarding the minify CSS option. So, to fix this issue I had to put the file "/wp-content/plugins/woocommerce/assets/css/woocommerce-smallscreen.css" inside the "Never minify the following CSS files" box.</p>
<p>But this is causing a strange problem for my theme. W3TC is now generating 2 minified CSS files. One containing the CSS files until the woocommerce-smallscreen.css file was detected, and one with the rest of the CSS files.</p>
<p>The problem with the second minified CSS file which is loaded after the inline CSS generated by the theme customizer.</p>
<p>The theme creator says he is not experiencing this behaviour. </p>
<p>What could cause this?</p>
